{"summary": "Initialize Python project with pyproject.toml, src/hello_app/main.py, and tests/test_smoke.py", "project": {"language": "python"}, "files": [{"path": "pyproject.toml", "content": "[build-system]
requires = ["setuptools>=61.0"]
build-backend = "setuptools.build_meta"

[project]
name = "hello-app"
version = "0.1.0"
description = "A simple hello world app"
requires-python = ">=3.8"

[tool.setuptools.packages.find]
where = ["src"]
"}, {"path": "src/hello_app/main.py", "content": "def get_message() -> str:
    return "hello world"
"}, {"path": "tests/test_smoke.py", "content": "import unittest
from hello_app.main import get_message

class TestSmoke(unittest.TestCase):
    def test_get_message(self):
        self.assertEqual(get_message(), "hello world")

if __name__ == "__main__":
    unittest.main()
"}], "dependencies": {"dependencies": {}, "devDependencies": {}, "python": [], "pythonDev": ["unittest"], "rust": [], "go": [], "cpp": []}, "commands": ["python -m unittest tests.test_smoke"]}
